snippet: Negotiations over fees paid by cable and satellite distributors to TV stations were largely successful, but in New York a dispute led to a blackout of the sports channel MSG.
abstract: Negotiations over fees paid by cable and satellite distributors to television stations are largely successful as deals were set to expire on Jan 1, but in New York a dispute leads to a blackout of the sports channel MSG; several other blackouts occur in other areas.
lead_paragraph: Negotiations over fees paid by cable and satellite distributors to TV stations were largely successful, but in New York a dispute led to a blackout of the sports channel MSG.

headline.seo: Cable TV Fee Disputes Cause a Few Blackouts
headline.main: In New York and Elsewhere, Disputes Over Television Fees Lead to a Few Blackouts
headline.print_headline: In New York and Elsewhere, Disputes Over Television Fees Lead to a Few Blackouts
